DESCRIPTION:

Steps to Install and Configure Flutter SDK:

Download Flutter SDK:
Download the latest stable Flutter SDK from the official link:
https://storage.googleapis.com/flutter_infra_release/releases/stable/windows/flutter_windows_3.13.7-stable.zip

Extract the Zip File:
Extract the downloaded zip file and move it to a suitable location, for example:
C:\development\flutter
(Do not place it in C:\Program Files\ to avoid permission issues.)

Set Flutter Path Environment Variable:

Open Edit environment variables for your account.

Under User variables, locate the variable Path.

Add a new entry for the Flutter bin folder path:
C:\development\flutter\bin

Verify Installation using Flutter Doctor:
Open Command Prompt and run the command:

flutter doctor


This command checks for all required tools and dependencies.

Install Android Studio:

Download from https://developer.android.com/studio
.

During setup, select Android Virtual Device for emulator support.

After installation, open Android Studio → Go to Plugins → Search and install Flutter.

It will automatically prompt to install Dart → Click Install → Restart IDE.

Accept Android Licenses:
Run the following command in CMD:

flutter doctor --android-licenses


Type y to accept all licenses.

(Optional) Install Visual Studio:

Download Visual Studio 2022 from https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/downloads/
.

Select the Desktop development with C++ workload during installation.

This step is required only for Windows desktop app development.

Final Verification:
Run the command again to confirm setup:

flutter doctor


Ensure all checks show a green tick (√) and “No issues found!”

OUTPUT:
C:\Users\blup>flutter doctor
Doctor summary (to see all details, run flutter doctor -v):
[√] Flutter (Channel stable, 2.10.4, on Microsoft Windows [Version 10.0.19041.746], locale en-US)
[√] Android toolchain - develop for Android devices (Android SDK version 32.1.0-rc1)
[√] Chrome - develop for the web
[√] Visual Studio - develop for Windows (Visual Studio Community 2022 17.1.3)
[√] Android Studio (version 2021.1)
[√] Connected device (2 available)
[√] HTTP Host Availability

• No issues found!


✅ Result:
Flutter and Dart SDK successfully installed and configured on Windows.
System is ready for cross-platform app development using Flutter.
